# Custom Diagram Canvas with Konva (P2 #7)

**Priority:** P2 (Medium)
**Estimated Time:** 15-18 hours
**Status:** Planning
**Created:** 2025-11-26
**Approach:** Hybrid - Konva for canvas abstraction, custom diagram logic

---

## Overview

Build a **custom diagram editor** using Konva (~50KB) for canvas primitives while implementing 100% custom diagram logic, tools, and features. This provides 90% ownership while leveraging battle-tested canvas abstractions for pan/zoom/rendering.

## Philosophy & Build vs Buy Decision

**Why Hybrid (Konva + Custom Logic):**
1. **90% Our Code** - Konva only handles low-level canvas (zoom, pan, transforms)
2. **100% Feature Control** - We own all diagram logic, tools, elements, connectors
3. **MIT Licensed** - Commercial use allowed, can sell platform
4. **Architectural Freedom** - Can add any feature from any competitor
5. **Not Copy-Paste** - This is genuinely OUR diagram editor, not wrapping someone else's
6. **Small Dependency** - Konva ~50KB (vs Excalidraw ~800KB+)
7. **Pride Factor** - We built the diagram editor, just used a canvas library (like using D3 for graph layout)

**What We Own (90%):**
- All diagram logic and business rules
- All tools (select, shapes, pen, connectors)
- All shape primitives and rendering
- All connector routing and smart snapping
- All export logic (PNG, SVG, PDF)
- All persistence and data model
- All UI/UX (toolbar, properties, layers)
- All keyboard shortcuts and interactions
- All future features (templates, AI, collaboration)

**What Konva Provides (10%):**
- Canvas element creation and management
- Mouse/touch event abstraction
- Pan/zoom/drag transformations
- Layer management and rendering pipeline
- Hit detection (which shape was clicked)
- Basic shape primitives (Rect, Circle, Line, Text as building blocks)

**Comparison to Other Library Usage:**
- **D3** - We use it for graph force simulation (utility algorithm), we own the graph feature
- **Recharts** - We use it for chart primitives, we own the analytics feature
- **Lexical** - We use it for rich text editing primitives, we own the notes feature
- **Konva** - We use it for canvas primitives, **we own the diagram feature**

**Why NOT Excalidraw:**
- Would be ~10% our code, 90% Excalidraw's feature implementation
- We'd be wrapping/extending their diagram editor, not building our own
- Less architectural control (must fit their design)
- Larger bundle (~800KB+ vs ~50KB)

**Alignment with CLAUDE.md:**
- ✅ "Build the best custom platform we can"
- ✅ "Forever continue to build onto"
- ✅ "Legally allowed to sell for profit" (MIT license)
- ✅ "Feel proud about being custom built"
- ✅ "Not copy-paste entire features" (konva is just canvas utility)

