## Technical Architecture

### Canvas Strategy: Konva

**Why Konva:**
- Small footprint (~50KB gzipped)
- MIT licensed (commercial use OK)
- React bindings (react-konva)
- Handles canvas complexity (events, transforms, hit detection)
- Battle-tested (used by major apps)
- We still own 90% of the code

**What Konva Does:**
- Canvas element management
- Pan/zoom via Stage
- Drag/transform via Transformer
- Event system (click, drag, wheel)
- Layer rendering
- Hit detection (which shape clicked)

**What We Build (Our Code):**
- All diagram business logic
- All tool implementations
- All connector routing
- All export logic
- All persistence
- All UI components
- All keyboard shortcuts
- All shape configurations

### Data Model

**Diagram:**
```typescript
interface Diagram {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
  thumbnail?: string; // base64 PNG

  // Canvas state
  canvasState: CanvasState;

  // Elements (our custom format)
  elements: DiagramElement[];

  // Metadata
  tags?: string[];
  linkedNotes?: string[];
  linkedTasks?: string[];
}

interface CanvasState {
  zoom: number; // 1.0 = 100%
  pan: { x: number; y: number }; // viewport offset
  gridSize: number; // 20px default
  snapToGrid: boolean;
}

interface DiagramElement {
  id: string;
  type: 'rectangle' | 'circle' | 'ellipse' | 'triangle' | 'diamond' | 'line' | 'arrow' | 'text' | 'freehand' | 'connector';

  // Position & size
  x: number;
  y: number;
  width: number;
  height: number;
  rotation?: number; // degrees

  // Styling
  fill?: string; // hex color or 'transparent'
  stroke?: string;
  strokeWidth?: number;
  strokeStyle?: 'solid' | 'dashed' | 'dotted';
  cornerRadius?: number; // for rectangles

  // Text-specific
  text?: string;
  fontSize?: number;
  fontFamily?: string;
  fontWeight?: 'normal' | 'bold';
  textAlign?: 'left' | 'center' | 'right';

  // Connector-specific
  startPoint?: { x: number; y: number };
  endPoint?: { x: number; y: number };
  startShapeId?: string; // smart connector source
  endShapeId?: string; // smart connector target
  startArrow?: boolean;
  endArrow?: boolean;
  connectorType?: 'straight' | 'curved' | 'orthogonal';

  // Path-specific (freehand)
  points?: Array<{ x: number; y: number }>;

  // Z-index
  zIndex: number;
}
```

